The paper deals with Multiagent Reinforcement Learning, which is a subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG) that focuses on agents learning to interact with each other in a shared environment. The paper also introduces an evolutionary algorithm for optimizing the global objective, which falls under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Evolutionary Computation (cs.NE). The paper specifically addresses problems related to multiagent coordination, which is a subfield of Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) and Control Systems (cs.SY).
